THE Hawks in Mpumalanga are searching for murder suspect Rassie Nkuna. He allegedly shot and killed a police officer and her sister on Sunday, 15 May, at Kanyamazane outside Mbombela. According to Captain Dineo Lucy Sekgotodi, it’s alleged that there was a dispute between Nkuna and his girlfriend, Marcia Mazibuko (43). “Sergeant Pretty Mazibuko (42), who is the girlfriend’s sister, tried to calm the situation when Nkuna drew his firearm and shot both of them. “They were rushed to a nearby clinic where they were certified dead on arrival,” Sekgotodi said. ALSO READ: WhatsApp premium set to launch soon! She said the suspect fled the scene and the incident was reported to the police. “A warrant for his arrest has been issued.” She urged anyone who knows his whereabouts to contact  investigating officer Lieutenant-Colonel Steve Msiza on 082 304 0171, or Warrant Officer Mduduzi Mutubatse on 072 195 0185. Alternatively, residents can call CrimeStop on 08600 10111.